BGP Multi-AS Lab – Three Routers
-------------------------------------------------
This lab simulates a multi-AS BGP network:

R1 (AS 6500) – Edge network with LAN (192.168.10.0/24)

R2 (AS 65001) – Transit router

R3 (AS 65002) – Edge network with LAN (192.168.40.0/24)

Objectives:

Configure point-to-point links

Configure LANs and PCs

Establish BGP neighbors across multiple ASes

Test end-to-end connectivity between LAN PCs
--------------------------------------------------------
IP Addressing Table
Link/Network	Device	IP Address	Subnet Mask
R1 ↔ R2	R1	192.168.20.1	255.255.255.250
	R2	192.168.20.2	255.255.255.250
R2 ↔ R3	R2	192.168.30.1	255.255.255.250
	R3	192.168.30.2	255.255.255.250
R1 LAN	R1	192.168.10.1	255.255.255.0
	PC1	192.168.10.10	255.255.255.0
	PC2	192.168.10.11	255.255.255.0
R3 LAN	R3	192.168.40.1	255.255.255.0
	PC1	192.168.40.20	255.255.255.0
	PC2	192.168.40.21	255.255.255.0
---------------------------------------------------------
Router Configurations
R1 (AS 6500)
enable
conf t
!
interface g0/0.10
 encapsulation dot1Q 10
 ip address 192.168.10.1 255.255.255.0
 no shutdown
!
interface g0/1
 ip address 192.168.20.1 255.255.255.252
 no shutdown
!
router bgp 6500
 neighbor 192.168.20.2 remote-as 65001
 network 192.168.10.0 mask 255.255.255.0
!
end

R2 (AS 65001)
enable
conf t
!
interface g0/0
 ip address 192.168.20.2 255.255.255.252
 no shutdown
!
interface g0/1
 ip address 192.168.30.1 255.255.255.252
 no shutdown
!
router bgp 65001
 neighbor 192.168.20.1 remote-as 6500
 neighbor 192.168.30.2 remote-as 65002
 network 192.168.20.0 mask 255.255.255.252
 network 192.168.30.0 mask 255.255.255.252
!
end

R3 (AS 65002)
enable
conf t
!
interface g0/0
 ip address 192.168.30.2 255.255.255.252
 no shutdown
!
interface g0/1.40
 encapsulation dot1Q 40
 ip address 192.168.40.1 255.255.255.0
 no shutdown
!
router bgp 65002
 neighbor 192.168.30.1 remote-as 65001
 network 192.168.40.0 mask 255.255.255.0
!
end
